caption: I dont know why I didn't find this place sooner. Every thing was amazing. Food, drinks and ambience. I even took a whole chicken home that was also mouth watering delicious. I woke up dreaming about the meal I had. If I could give more than 5 stars I would.

Great food

Drinks and food are great, prices are reasonable, service is fast.
Ordered take-out and was happy with the food and service. Ordered the French toast, pastries, western omelette and fried chicken with scallion waffles. We weren’t disappointed.

delicious, y’all. i ordered the grilled hanger steak- medium, w asparagus and chili linguine. had it delivered through uber eats and it was about as good as a take out steak dinner can get. steak temperature was perfect. asparagus was cooked perfectly. and the chili linguine was so complimentary. will def order from here again!

Great Mayo on my BLT!

Tomato & mozz panini was perf. Med slice tomato, handful of arugula, and thin layer of mozz. Get it extra toasted for added crunch 👌🏼  Didn’t try the chicken but tried the waffles. So so good. Bits of scallion & cheese topped off w/ powdered sugar. Perf balance of sweet and savory  Mac & cheese: very gooey and cheesy. Macaroni cooked perfectly. Not too soft, not al dente. Justtt right. Also, did I mention VERY CHEESEY?!

Omg, the food is so delicious 😩😋❤️🙌🏾 I just had the collard greens, home fries and rotisserie chicken.... Everything was well seasoned and cooked to perfection. I will order again. Thank you!

After having Zaca Cafe's AMAZING pot pies for the first time, I was hooked. They're so warm, cozy, and taste like home. I told a friend about them while visiting his apartment and he was bummed they weren't in his delivery radius, so I decided we'd have a pot pie night and he came over. Adja(and the chef) went -above and beyond- to make sure we got our food and it was SO DELICIOUS. All of us were in heaven. Pot pie night is definitely going to be a recurring thing. Thank you for being so amazing (:
Friendly staff, good coffee. Would strongly recommend their almond croissant.
Love Zaca! Such a gem in our hood, great food, menu, & service🙏🏽

I just reheated my crits and I had to come to the review section to tell the world how AMAZING the food is from Zaca Cafe. I don't think there is one item off the menu that isn't prepared and seasoned to perfection! Whether it's breakfast, lunch or dinner that you are looking for, this place is it. And while some people complain about the wait being too long, ask yourself would you rather your food rushed or actually cooked properly.
Best grits I’ve ever had- outstanding. Got the Zaca platter and the tomato jam and salsa verde were so delish. Highly recommend!

The food is good and filling. The reason why it only gets a 3/5 is the wait time. It takes a good while (almost 40 mins) for an order and it seems they prioritize take-out orders. Id give them a chance but they'd have a better rating if the made meals based on when you order vs whats easier to make.
I can’t stop ordering from Zaca cafe. The hanger steak panini is my fav it’s soooooo good & fresh I haven’t fount time to try anything else. I will make time to try the salmon burger soon 🥰
Best burger

The food here is fantastic. I ordered Kale Caesar salad (delicious and herbed creamy caesar dressing and the croutons were homemade) and I had the BEST BLT EVER- crunchy bacon, crisp lettuce, herbed mayo, fresh tomato, and perfectly toasted multigrain bread. When they did not have something I ordered, a representative from the restaurant called me and informed me SUPER sweet and personable staff. I will definitely be ordering from here again.

so blessed to have brought my grandfather here to celebrate his 82nd birthday as well as experience the goodness that your hands prepared for us...they even accommodated us before their opening time 🙌🏽🙌🏽...many blessings and success to your business
Amazing food and service, always.

Thank You Zaca, Finally a place where my chicken is properly seasoned. I ordered rotisserie chicken and she got the chicken skewers and the kale salad .. mmmmmmmm!!!!!!! Everything was delicious and perfectly cooked.. even my picky daughter enjoyed her meal... Kudos to you guys.. This will be not be my last meal from you!!!!!

I am obsessed with Zaca Cafe!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! It was by chance I tried it and now I can’t stop. You can taste pure love in everything they make; haven’t tasted anything I didn’t like. NYC falls short when it comes to grits and Zaca makes them p e r f e c t l y ! Salmon, pot pie, and all the sides are bomb, too. Perhaps don’t order if you’re in a rush, they make things right and that takes time, but I wouldn’t have it any other way. ❤️

I really hate to rate this place so low but I did not have the best experience here. It took them 25 minutes to finally take our order even though I told them 3 times that we were ready to order. When they finally took our order, I see that they got my smoothie wrong (I ordered mango and banana, they added a ton of blueberries and then asked me if I was okay with it). How do you screw that up?  Then the French toast that I ordered was burnt on some sides with the strawberries incredibly soggy. I am not sure if it was laziness that made them think it was a good idea to microwave strawberries but I was not feeling it.  Also, it was very cold and every time the door opened and closed, the whole restaurant was blasted with cold air. Please put an enclosure/divider outside of the door.  Overall, I could tell that they were trying their best and the servers were definitely sweet. But combined with the long wait, burnt food and just plain ol’ clumsiness, I will not come here again. Maybe their to-go section of the restaurant is better. I still will not be coming back to find out.

The food is really good. Especially the chicken and waffle and Zaca Burger. The seasoning they mix in with the waffle batter is really tasty and pretty unique. So with that being said, the service is pretty eh. I’ve had to get up and ask for my check twice due to them taking forever and actually left and went to another spot another time, because it took them so long to take my order. Don’t get it wrong, I’m a very patient dude and the server knew I was there because she gave me a menu. But if there’s barely anyone there and you’re off in the other part of the shop and have me waiting 10 minutes, then I’m good. But like I said, the food is good though. Service....meh.

Our favorite restaurant during our stay in New York. We went here several times, for breakfast and lunch, as well as for dinner. Such delicious food, hospitable employees and a good vibe. Wish I would have Zaca around the corner at home.

Salmon burger was amazing!! The flavors meshed together beautifully. Each bite was a pleasant surprise. I look forward to enjoying more items from Zaca Cafe.

Enjoyed a wonderful meal here today. Why was it wonderful? The chef and waitress were personable and handled me and my boyfriend with care. We were welcomed and seated immediately. The drip coffee was delicious.  We also ordered salmon burgers and the zaca salads which were also delicious and very fresh. The ambience is small, was clean and friendly. Considering how many new cafes are in the neighborhood, its not that easy to find a great cup of coffee in a down to earth atsmosphere. ZACA Cafe offers all of that in the perfect neighborhood spot. Grab a pastry and espresso drink on the run or if youre busy, enjoy their spacious seating and free WiFi. The chocolate-pecan cookie can easily upstage Levain's (get it toasted), and if Vanessa is there, you are guarunteed incredible customer service. Its stand out, for sure. (So leave a big tip!)
Great food, friendly people
Good food and good people. A few dollars more than it should be.

This place is just what the neighborhood needed. I'm still yet to have a bad bite or sip of anything, the atmosphere is inviting, and the staff - though busy - is warm and friendly. The hangar steak panini is one of the best sandwiches I've had in Bed-Stuy, the Zaca platter is a perfect "this week has been ROUGH" Saturday brunch meal to make you feel healthy and satisfied, and every carb from croissant to waffle has been perfect. The decor feels distinctly cross cultural, as a strong West African motif dances with a few "new Brooklyn" fixtures, like a changing chalk-marker menu wall, and Edison-bulb hanging lights. With great prices, a great atmosphere, black-ownership, and delicious food, this place is an absolute treat, and quickly becoming one of my neighborhood favorites for a sit-down down meal or a couple hours of laptop work.
A creative and delicious menu with a beautiful theme. My salmon sandwich was amazing and I’m already planning my next trip. Thanks for the great service and experience !

Yaa noogo! Stopped in because we heard a burkinabe had opened a restaurant in our neck of the woods. We were so excited to see all the West African-inspired decor! It’s really an Instagram worthy cafe. Also the food was amazing. Not a big fan of kale but I would go back there for that Kale Caesar salad!

A true Brooklyn gem. Visiting NYC but staying in Bed Stuy and absolutely loving our visits to Zaca. From service to quality of food this place has set a new bar for a neighborhood spot. Sad that I have to leave Zaca behind at the culmination of the trip. A must visit for visitors as well as the NYC residents.

I'm a self proclaimed food snob so when I say Zaca has the best fish sandwich I've ever had theres some real weight to my review.  A substantial sandwich, well seasoned, delicately cooked, with cucumber and pickled ginger. Just delicious. I also had the chicken and waffles and they were tasty.  Nice atmosphere and music inside. Great service with a smile and talented chef. A great addition to Bed Stuy!

Best food in BedStuy Brooklyn.  Everything on the menu is excellent. The head chef is heavily influenced by French cuisine and all of his dishes are well thought out. They just opened so I can always get a table. Once the word spreads about this place, it will be standing room only.

I’ve had both takeout & eat-in (with my 10 yr old grandson) & both were very very positive experiences.  My grandson had the pot pie & it was lukewarm when served but delicious.
